@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Dementia Care";
}

<div class="container-fluid no-padding">
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding full-height">
            <img src="~/Images/background.jpg" class="img-fit" alt="Dementia Care" />

            <div class="sticky-top abs-position full-width">
                <img src="~/Images/title.png" class="img-center" alt="" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding">
            <div class="card bg-dark" style="border:0px; border-radius: 0px;">
                <div class="card-text">
                    <h5 class="text-white text-break text-center calibri-font dc-margin-padding">
                        Dementia is a major health problem in Australia. It has profound consequences for the health and quality of
                        life of people with the condition, as well as for their families and friends.
                    </h5>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 patients-chart">
            <div id="dementiaPopulationChart" class="calibri-font"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding">
            <div class="card bg-dark" style="border:0px; border-radius: 0px;">
                <div class="card-text">
                    <h5 class="text-white text-break text-center calibri-font dc-margin-padding">
                        At present, there are 400,833 elders living with dementia in Australia and this number is projected to reach
                        1.1 million people by 2056. Majority of this people – approximately 75% - live in community homes and 90% of
                        them are cared by family members (spouse/children), where most patients need self-care assistance.
                    </h5>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-lg-6 patients-chart">
            <div id="assistanceChart" class="calibri-font"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 patients-chart">
            <div id="carerChart" class="calibri-font"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding">
            <div class="card bg-dark" style="border:0px; border-radius: 0px;">
                <div class="card-text">
                    <h5 class="text-white text-break text-center calibri-font dc-margin-padding">
                        Our aim is to provide a solution that makes life easier not only for recently diagnosed dementia patients but
                        also for carers who are part of their daily lives.
                        <br /><br />
                        | IT for Social Good |
                    </h5>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-lg-4 no-padding">
            <div class="card" style="border: 0px; border-radius:0px;">
                <img src="~/Images/first.jpg" class="card-img-top" style="border-radius:0px;" alt="Stimulus" />
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title calibri-font">&diams; STIMULUS (PAVLOVIAN THEORY)</h5>
                    <p class="text-break calibri-font">
                        Pavlovian theory is a learning procedure that involves pairing a stimulus with a conditioned response. Our
                        solution involves training patients minds to an external stimulus with a preconditioned involuntary cognitive
                        response. Stimulation include - Being hydrated, having meals and medicine on time.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 no-padding">
            <div class="card" style="border: 0px; border-radius:0px;">
                <img src="~/Images/second.jpg" class="card-img-top" style="border-radius:0px;" alt="Stimulus" />
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title calibri-font">&diams; PUZZLE</h5>
                    <p class="text-break calibri-font">
                        Another part of our solution includes patients solving puzzles, where solution of puzzles is an image/picture
                        uploaded/selected by carers. The benefit is trying to make patients remember old memories and initiate
                        conversation between patient and carer.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-4 no-padding">
            <div class="card" style="border: 0px; border-radius:0px;">
                <img src="~/Images/third.jpg" class="card-img-top" style="border-radius:0px;" alt="Stimulus" />
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title calibri-font">&diams; AUGMENTED REALITY</h5>
                    <p class="text-break calibri-font">
                        Lastly, we try creating fun and lively interaction between patients and carers with the use of AR technology.
                        We use 3D AR objects and place it into real world using smart devices, which are interactable. This will help
                        create new memories for family members and friends.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding">
            <div class="card" style="border-left: 0px; border-right: 0px; border-radius: 0px;">
                <img src="~/Images/applogo.png" style="max-width: 250px; display: block; margin: auto;" alt="Play Store" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row no-margin">
        <div class="col-12 no-padding">
            <div class="card bg-dark" style="border:0px; border-radius: 0px;">
                <div class="card-text">
                    <h5 class="text-white text-break text-center calibri-font dc-margin-padding">
                        DEVELOPED &amp; DESIGNED BY AUG.life
                    </h5>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

